business insights such as:
Best-selling products and categories
Monthly & seasonal sales trends
Customer behavior (new vs returning customers)
Revenue contribution by region
Impact of discounts on revenue and profitability
The final outcome is an interactive dashboard built using Power BI / Tableau / Excel, enabling business stakeholders to make data-driven decisions.

Tools & Technologies
Category	Tools
Data Cleaning & Analysis	Excel / Python (optional)
Visualization	Power BI / Tableau / Excel Pivot Charts
Dataset Source	Kaggle — “E-Commerce Sales Dataset”

Dataset
The dataset includes information about:
Order ID
Customer ID
Product Name / Category
Quantity
Unit Price / Discount
Order Date
Shipping Region / State
Profit & Revenue
Dataset not included due to licensing rules — search on Kaggle for: “Sample Superstore” or “E-Commerce Sales Dataset.”

Project Workflow
Data Acquisition
Download dataset from Kaggle
Import into Excel or Power BI

Data Cleaning
Handle missing or inconsistent values
Convert date to proper format
Standardize product names & categories

Feature Engineering
Create calculated fields:
Total Sales = Quantity × Unit Price
Profit Margin %
Customer Type = New / Returning

Exploratory Analysis
Identify product and category trends
Study seasonality and yearly growth
Analyze customer segments and behavior

Dashboard Creation
KPIs (Revenue, Profit, Orders, Avg Order Value)
Interactive filters (Region, Product Category, Time Period)
Visuals: Bar charts, line charts, maps, pie charts



Future Enhancements
Deploy dashboard online for public access
Predict future demand using forecasting models
Add customer segmentation using clustering (RFM analysis)

 Installation Instructions
If using Power BI:
No installation needed — open the .pbix file.
If analyzing with Python (optional):
git clone https://github.com/your-username/ecommerce-sales-analysis
cd ecommerce-sales-analysis
pip install -r requirements.txt

